📌 PDF Merger – Overview

This is a simple Python mini project that allows users to merge multiple PDF files into a single document using the PyPDF2 library.

🎯 Features

Takes input for the number of PDFs to merge.

Lets the user enter file names (or full file paths).

Combines all selected PDFs into one single output file.

Handles errors gracefully (e.g., missing files, wrong paths).

Saves the final merged PDF as merged-pdf.pdf.

🛠️ Technologies Used

Python 3

PyPDF2 library

🚀 How It Works

The program asks the user how many PDFs they want to merge.

The user enters the names/paths of the PDF files.

The program appends each PDF in the given order.

Finally, it creates a new file called merged-pdf.pdf.

A success message is displayed after completion.

✅ Example
How many PDF's do you want to merge?
3
Enter the path/name of PDF 1: file1.pdf
Enter the path/name of PDF 2: file2.pdf
Enter the path/name of PDF 3: file3.pdf

✅ Successfully merged 3 PDFs into 'merged-pdf.pdf'

📂 Output

A single merged PDF file named merged-pdf.pdf containing all input files in the given order.